description: Aspose.Diagram is a class library for working with Microsoft Visio files. It allows developers to create new diagrams and work with VSD, VSDX, VSTX, VSSX, VSS, VST, VSX, VTX, VDW and VDX files on ASP.NET web applications, web services and Windows applications. It allows you to open files and manipulate the elements of the diagram, from lines and fills, to more complex elements, and then export to VDX, VSX,VSDX,VSSX,VSTX, VTX, XPS, HTML, SVG, SWF, XAML, image or PDF formats.
releaseNotes:
This release introduces the features, enhancements,task and bug fixes as detailed below:
    
    New Features
   DIAGRAMNET-50739-Add support of detecting the Visio diagram type
   DIAGRAMNET-50746-Prevent export of the hidden Visio pages in the PDF
   DIAGRAMNET-50747-Prevent export of the hidden Visio pages in the HTML
   DIAGRAMNET-50750-Prevent export of the hidden Visio pages in the PNG
   DIAGRAMNET-50751-Prevent export of the hidden Visio pages in the JPEG
   DIAGRAMNET-50752-Prevent export of the hidden Visio pages in the SVG
   DIAGRAMNET-50753-Prevent export of the hidden Visio pages in the GIF
   DIAGRAMNET-50754-Prevent export of the hidden Visio pages in the XPS
          
    Enhancements
   DIAGRAMNET-50541-VSDX to PDF conversion, Hebrew text items are rendered in reverse order
   DIAGRAMNET-50542-VSD to PDF conversion, Arabic word turns into letters
   
    Bugs      

   DIAGRAMNET-50682-VSD to PDF export, the table cell's text is partially invisible
   DIAGRAMNET-50712-VDX to PDF export - the text of various shapes is misplaced
   DIAGRAMNET-50741-VSD to SVG export is missing some Visio shapes
   DIAGRAMNET-50742-VSD to SVG export is not applying the inner white color of shapes
   DIAGRAMNET-50744-Open and save routine of VSDX changes text into dummy characters
   DIAGRAMNET-50745-Open and save routine of VSDX has changed the dotted line shaper
   DIAGRAMNET-50748-VSD to PDF export - the text items are misplaced
   DIAGRAMNET-50763-VSD to VDX export is throwing the Master element error
